author: kfogel
msg: Reformat the code to use a consistent no-space-before-param-list-paren style.

Subject: Results of: [VOTE] New space-before-parens style

I took the opportunity to make spacing among all parens in SVN_ERR
macro calls consistent.  But I did not address consistency of casts,
nor whether a function name should always appear below its return type
in declarations and definitions, nor whether there should be a space
before/after the "*" when declaring pointer return types.
* www/hacking.html
(coding-style): Document that we are no-space-before-paren now.
* everywhere: Reformat.

author: pburba
msg: OS400/EBCDIC Port: Disable svn:executable automatic property setting.
This is one of several patches to allow Subversion to run on
IBM's OS400 V5R4.
The OS400's IFS (Integrated File System) supports unix-like file
permissions.  However, the executable permission has no real meaning
on the iSeries.  This becomes a problem when creating or copying a
file to the IFS via a mapped Windows drive or with the IBM Rational
Software Development Platform (two common practices) because in these
cases the resulting files have permissions set at -rwxrwxrwx by
default.  To avoid svn:executable getting set on every svn add(ed)
file this patch turns off that automatic property setting.
Approved by: Julian Foad <julianfoad@btopenworld.com>
* subversion/libsvn_client/add.c
(svn_client__get_auto_props): Don't automatically set
svn:executable property on added files.

author: jerenkrantz
msg: Move PROPFIND requests into their own serf buckets so that we can delay
creation of the body until request delivery time.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/property.c
(handle_propfind): Delay creation of the Expat instance until we need it
and clear it after we're done.
(check_cache): Move session lookup cache code to here.
(deliver_propfind): Split out most of the code into check_cache() and
the new PROPFIND bucket.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/ra_serf.h
(propfind_context_t): Add string version of revision.
(serf_bucket_propfind_create): Declare creator for PROPFIND bucket.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/util.c
(handle_xml_parser): Do not free Expat parser here.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/propfind_buckets.c
(added): New bucket type that creates a PROPFIND request body.
